     1|/**
     2| * IVX Owner Auth Proxy — Backend-mediated Supabase authentication.
     3| *
     4| * The production backend has SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY but is missing
     5| * EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY. This proxy lets the iOS app authenticate
     6| * through the backend using the service role key, so owner login works
     7| * even when the anon key is not configured on Render.
     8| *
     9| * Security:
    10| *   - Uses service role key ONLY for Supabase admin operations
    11| *   - Never returns the service role key
    12| *   - Returns the user's own access/refresh token (not a secret)
    13| *   - Rate-limited per IP + email
    14| *   - Password validation matches the V7 registration rules
    15| *
    16| * Endpoints:
    17| *   POST /api/ivx/owner-auth/login     — email + password → session tokens
    18| *   POST /api/ivx/owner-auth/refresh   — refresh token → new session
    19| *   POST /api/ivx/owner-auth/recover   — email → password reset email
    20| *   POST /api/ivx/owner-auth/repair    — email + newPassword → V7 full repair
    21| *   GET  /api/ivx/owner-auth/diagnostic — backend auth readiness probe
    22| */
